    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Michigan Commission on Reform and Modernization of Government was established by Governor Frank Murphy in 1938. The commission was headed by University of Michigan political science professor J.R. Hayden.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The record group includes proceedings of the commission, final report to the governor with drafts and revisions, correspondence, clippings, press releases, and bill submitted to the legislature with the report</p>
    </scopecontent>
